<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1923-12-19T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1923-12-19T16:00:00-05:00" n="376" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d376">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">815.00/2788: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Honduras</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Morales</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tegucigalpa</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-12-19T15:00:00-06:00"><hi rend="italic">December 19,
                                        1923—3 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 10:23
                            p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>107. Over 200 of the Carias leaders have been arrested in different parts
                            of the country since yesterday. One Congressman was killed and another
                            [person?] arrested by Government officers’ forces. The latter is a
                            Justice of the Supreme Court.</p>
                        <p>It would appear that the Government’s defense has now turned out to be
                            persecution.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Morales</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>